    nr 'That first breath I spoke of did its work to jump-start my senses.'
    nr 'The smell of metal, the stink of preserving fluid and formaldehyde…'
    nr '…and the scent of blood and flesh were like a cheese grater against my senses'
    nr 'The lighting was dim and my vision blurry, but here and there I could hear the shuffling of feet and the creak of dry joints.'
